communications.subject: Texas Public Information Act Request: Ora Wood 1979 Probate Documents
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

All probate documents relating to Ora Wood (née Paine), who passed in 1979.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Katie King

communications.subject: Virginia Freedom of Information Act Request: Count of Competency Evaluations
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Virginia Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

My request pertains to obtaining information from the regarding data from Office of the Executive Secretary concerning  records of reimbursements for court-ordered competency evaluations. Specifically, I am requesting monthly counts of court-ordered competency evaluations by court, if such data is available. If monthly counts are not available, then annual counts for each court are acceptable. I would like this data for as far back as the Office of the Executive Secretary has it available. If this data can be separated into just competency evaluations vs combination competency and sanity at the time of offense evaluations, then I would ask that these counts go in separate columns.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Tom Nash, a citizen of Virginia, in coordination with Brandon Morrissey.
